# <type>[optional scope]: <description>
#
# [optional body]
#
# [optional footer(s)]

# --- COMMIT END ---
# Remember to:
# * Capitalize the subject line
# * Use Australian English spelling (colour, centre, organisation)
# * Use the imperative mood in the subject line ("add", not "added")
# * Do not end the subject line with a period
# * Separate subject from body with a blank line
# * Use the body to explain what and why vs. how
# * Can include multiple paragraphs in body
#
# Type can be:
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   docs     (documentation)
#   style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#   refactor (refactoring production code)
#   test     (adding tests, refactoring test; no production code change)
#   chore    (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc; no production code change)
#   perf     (performance improvements)
#   ci       (CI/CD changes)
#   build    (build system changes)
#   revert   (revert previous changes)
#
# Scope examples:
#   (frontend), (backend), (api), (database), (auth), (ui), (tests)
#
# Subject line examples:
#   feat(auth): add JWT token validation
#   fix(api): correct user profile endpoint response
#   docs: update README with installation instructions
#   style(frontend): format React components with Prettier
#   refactor(database): optimise query performance
#   test(api): add integration tests for user endpoints
#   chore: update dependencies to latest versions
#
# Breaking changes:
#   feat!: drop support for Node.js 16
#   feat(api)!: change user ID format to UUID
#
# Australian English reminders:
#   - colour not color
#   - centre not center
#   - organisation not organization
#   - realise not realize
#   - behaviour not behavior